      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BIGBAD ESME (8) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at this track over 388m behind Any Ace Bronte (23.32) in a Grade 5. Was a winner prior to that. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Can atone. MY CAPE ESCAPE (1) was failed to finish in a Grade 5 two back then given a three months break after failing to finish at Gunnedah last time. Has the ability and looks a key chance. CHIEF ENFORCER (4) has a strong winning strike-rate this journey here having won two of three starts. Was out of the placings last time (23.58) at The Gardens in a Grade 5, finishing fourth and beaten 5.5 lengths. With even luck and a clean start can sneak into the finish. STAR ZIPPER (3) was a winner two back and strongly fancied last time but could only manage fourth (19.21) at Q Straight.",
